first start the Instance in AWS
then connect the ec2 instance in terminal using
       ssh -i <keyPair_name> ec2-user@<public_ip of instance>
and switch to root user using 
       sudo su
once connected, Update the package using
       yum update -y
then install docker using
       yum install docker -y
then start the docker service using
       service docker start
then play with some docker commands
       docker version
       docker images
       docker ps
then i'll try to install nginx image from dockerhub using pull command
       docker pull nginx:latest
then create and run a container from that image
       docker run nginx.
lists all containers
       docker ps -a.
